The boy told police: 'I always thought he would really be a good dad to me, I liked him. Now everything is ruined. I don't know why he did this, he just seemed to become someone else.'

Wang apologised and admitted to committing the crime at the Shenyang Intermediate People's Court.

His lawyer argued Wang acted 'out of impulse' and asked for a lenient sentence.

In handing him only 11 years in prison instead of life, the court  agreed to this request after hearing that he had showed contrition and been forgiven by the boy's family.

